 ilog2, and<br />the result is undefined<br /><br />   You never check for errors. There's a check for tk-&gt;size_shift ==<br />0, but is that actually the guaranteed return value of ilog2(0)? No.<br /><br /> - there is exactly one user of dev_pagemap_mapping_size(), and the above is it.<br /><br />   Why the hell didn't that function just return the number of bits to<br />begin with?<br /><br />I do not care if you screw up your own particular driver that much.<br /><br />But when I see a pull request with complete and utter garbage in the<br />core mm part, I will not pull.<br /><br />This is not acceptable.<br /><br />Pulled, merge conflict fixed, and then immediately unpulled again.<br /><br />I do not want to *EVER* see these kinds of patches to core MM code.<br />And I'm not gfoing to pull these patches or anythinig that looks like<br />it has any trace of this shit.<br /><br />I get upset, because dammit, I expect better. I don't want to go "oh,<br />this changes core code, let's just skim over the patches" and<br />immediately find something fundamentally broken like this.<br /><br />               Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
